##Shanghai medical team's first patient discharged from hospital. Ward Director Fang Bangjiang explains how TCM treats "acute diseases"

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Most of the 46 patients in the C5 ward taken over by Longhua Hospital and the City Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine have tested negative for COVID-19 nucleic acid for the first time after being treated by traditional Chinese medicine, the most severe two critical cases were treated with the strategy of "truncation and Torsion" . One patient was cured and the other was better than before.

By Zhou Jie

The first patient discharged from the hospital was cured by the Shanghai national team of Traditional Chinese Medicine on the 10th day of the arrival of the fourth national team of traditional Chinese medicine.

On February 25, the first batch of newly diagnosed pneumonia patients, Chan Mou, was discharged from the three departments and five wards of the Raytheon Mountain Hospital in Wuhan, which was set up by the Longhua Hospital affiliated to Shanghai University of Traditional Chinese medicine and the Shanghai Municipal Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Even more heartening was the fact that most of the 46 patients in the C5 ward taken over by Longhua Hospital and the City Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine had tested negative for COVID-19 after treatment with traditional Chinese medicine, the most severe two critical cases were treated with the strategy of "truncation and Torsion" . One patient was cured and the other was better than before.

At the end of the day, Fang Bangjiang, director of the Emergency Department at Longhua Hospital and Director of the C5 ward at Mount Thor, was interviewed by Xinmin Weekly. After the urgent delivery of the Hubei aid mission, over 50 years old, he volunteered for the first time. Although he had many old problems, he still worked more than 12 hours every day after he arrived in Wuhan.

He said he was ready for the final evacuation of Wuhan when the outbreak was completely under control.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: Tell me about the first patient who was discharged from the hospital. What was his treatment like?

Fang Bangjiang: When we took this one, he was having trouble breathing, and his blood pressure and his stats were dropping. According to the clinical characteristics of the patients, through clinical differentiation of symptoms and signs, we discuss that the main cause of the disease is the damp toxin epidemic disease, which belongs to the category of "damp-warm" , and is caused by "distemper up" , reduction of Fangpseudohuo Puxia Ling decoction.

After a few days of this treatment, his symptoms cleared up, and we did two nucleic acids tests, a CT scan, blood work, and then he was discharged.

We believe that Chinese and Western medicine complement each other, will make a breakthrough in the treatment of this disease, can the disease mortality rate and mild to moderate patients to develop critical illness rate to reduce it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: What are the characteristics of the patients at Thor Mountain? How does traditional Chinese medicine view new coronary pneumonia?

Fang Bangjiang: about 30% of the patients in our ward are seriously ill. In the treatment of traditional Chinese medicine is the main, supplemented by Western medicine, integrated Chinese and Western medicine.

Many people have the impression that TCM is a slow doctor who treats pre-existing diseases and chronic diseases. For example, we are all familiar with the practice of prescribing a plaster prescription to treat chronic diseases. In fact, TCM has always been able to play a huge role in treating acute and infectious diseases.

The existence of infectious diseases has been recognized since the time of Yellow Emperor. And in Wu youxing's book on Epidemic Febrile Diseases, written several hundred years ago, it is pointed out that "typhoid fever does not infect people, epidemic disease can infect people. The evil of typhoid fever enters from no orifices; the evil of epidemic disease enters from mouth and nose" . It means that we realized that the plague had two modes of transmission, air and contact, hundreds of years earlier than in the West. There were many infectious diseases in ancient Jiangsu area, which gave birth to many epidemic disease experts like Wu Youxing, Ye Tianshi and Wu Jutong.

Before there is no specific therapeutic drug for NCP, we should give full play to the advantages of traditional Chinese medicine in treating infectious diseases in critically ill patients. The combination of traditional Chinese and Western medicine has complementary advantages. I think it is very helpful for the treatment of this infectious disease.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: What are the specific treatment methods of traditional Chinese medicine?

Fang Bangjiang: Before coming to Wuhan, actually I had already participated in the treatment of new coronary pneumonia. Because I was studying in Hubei, Wuhan Major Hospitals have my classmates, students, the first time they contact me consultation.

With years of experience in treating infectious diseases, I gave them some advice, and it was comforting to know that more than 40 patients in one hospital, including all the critically ill, were getting better and not one died.

In addition, in order to prepare for the war in the affected areas as soon as possible, I have consulted a number of Chinese medical literature on the treatment of infectious diseases, and at the invitation of the People's Medical Publishing House, the group, which includes experts from the Hubei Epidemic area and the National Frontline, compiled and published the handbook of integrated Chinese and Western medicine for the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia during the Lunar New Year holiday. As far as the current epidemic situation is concerned, for most mild and ordinary patients, the effect of integrated Chinese and Western medicine is much better than that of Western medicine alone.

Traditional Chinese medicine is to pay attention to the overall concept, treatment based on syndrome differentiation, to vary from person to person and from time to time. Prior to coming to the mountain, I had drawn up different treatment plans for patients with mild, moderate or severe illness and critically ill patients, based on the national and Shanghai COVID-19. At present, we have a series of traditional Chinese medicine treatment methods, such as Chinese medicine, acupuncture and moxibustion, smokeless moxibustion, Meridian therapeutic apparatus, and Gongfa (Baduanjin) , recently, we have also worked with Professor Jia Lijun of Longhua Hospital and other rehabilitation treatments based on the theory of traditional Chinese medicine, traditional culture meditation, music therapy and psychological intervention, helps the patient to look positively positively the illness, promotes the illness recovery.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The patient was treated with electroacupuncture apparatus

Xinmin Weekly: What measures do we have for the seriously ill?

Fang Bangjiang: new coronary pneumonia has the characteristics of acute infectious diseases such as acute onset, rapid development, rapid change, severe disease, great threat, etc. . We through strengthen the body's immunity, through the adoption of a large number of nourishing Qi and Yin, improve his own immunity, achieved better results, improved clinical efficacy.

The most common severe and fatal causes of NCP are aspiration failure, shock and multiple organ failure, which belong to the category of "warm disease" in TCM, and the key pathogenic factors are "poison" and "stasis" , based on the traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM)"treating Febrile diseases not only early but also early" and "six Fu organs for general use" , in the early and middle stages, the methods of clearing away "poison" and "storing Yin under emergency" were adopted to protect the healthy Qi, prevent disease and change, and quickly cut off the trend of malignant development, also known as the "cut-off Torsion" prevention and control strategy. The treatment for Sepsis, which is a fatal organ dysfunction caused by infection, and severe cases of Multiple Organ Dysfunction Syndrome pneumonia, which is actually caused by Sepsis, was supported by a Major National R & D Program in 2018, i've used this strategy with these two patients so far, and it's helped two critically ill patients get better.

For patients with aspiration failure, on the basis of previous acupuncture treatment of senile cough and asthma by Shanghai Health Committee, we used acupuncture treatment to reduce or replace aspiration therapy, one of our patients was cured and his breathing returned to normal that night, avoiding the use of suction machines. Another patient who was supposed to be intubated, we ended up using non-invasive breathing machine, while using traditional Chinese medicine, acupuncture and other methods, the patient is now in good condition, with less time.

Our Ward 48 patients, our ward TCM treatment rate of 100% , after TCM treatment, the majority of patients with the first COVID-19 nucleic acid test results have been negative, all patients are improving one by one.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu Yanhong, secretary of the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine, paid a visit to the Shanghai Post

Xinmin Weekly: Mount Thor is a newly built hospital. What are the local hardware conditions after the arrival of the medical team? What did you do when you took over thor?

Fang Bangjiang: On the evening of February 14, the hospital issued an emergency notice, calling on all hospital staff to join the medical team to assist Hubei. In fact, I had this idea prepared for a long time, I have more than 30 years of Party members, the director of emergency medicine, long-term engaged in infectious diseases and critical illness research, is the national leader of Chinese Medicine "Qi Huang Scholars" , sooner or later. The other one, I am also from Hubei, and I was also employed as a "Chutian scholar" in Hubei Province. I knew quite a bit about the local customs and humanities in my hometown, so after the urgent notice came down, I applied for the position at the first opportunity, in the meantime, all of our E.R. attendings have signed up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We are the fourth group of Hubei National Medical Team, about 3:00 am to Wuhan, the day came a cold wave, the temperature suddenly dropped more than ten degrees, hotels can not open air conditioning, many people can't sleep.

Mount Thor is a makeshift hospital with few amenities. The hotel is an hour's drive from Mount Thor. The next morning, the team went to the Thor Mountain Hospital to check the situation, at that time can be said to be "nothing" , is an empty room, from the bed to the diagnosis and treatment equipment, we have to rely on everyone together to move, placement. The first day we busy to 12 o'clock at night, and then "decoration" a few days, the conditions of the ward adjusted to the hospital standards. By February 20th, we had our first patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A view of the department

Xinmin Weekly: What departments are the medical teams made up of?

Fang Bangjiang: This time we come to the medical team strength is very strong, most of the 8 doctors are engaged in serious respiratory disease, for such patients are very experienced. Our Ward and the Shanghai Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine Together, cooperation is very smooth, also do not care about hard and tired.

In fact, our medical staff really overcome many difficulties to participate in the aid of Hubei. We had a doctor, whose mother was also the head of the emergency department, who had assisted in Africa, and this time he had volunteered for the medical team, but his child was very young, and his father had recently been paralyzed in his bed, but the country needed him, and he came anyway. We also have a lot of 95 little girl nurses, secretly came to Wuhan, afraid that the family worried about not telling relatives.

We don't have enough manpower for this group of people to help Hubei. There are only over 60 medical and nursing staff in our ward, so doctors and nurses are working very hard and living far away from each other. Doctors, including travelling and working, work nearly 12 hours a day, i get up at 5 o'clock every day, take an hour bus to Thor Mountain Hospital, and sometimes arrive at the station after 12 o'clock at night. As the ward director, I am responsible for the overall work. Our colleagues at Longhua Hospital and the Municipal Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine work and live in a very harmonious way. The Municipal Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine leads the team. Director Feng Qimao and director Zhao Fancheng work very actively, ward just opened a lot of things are inseparable from me, including the establishment of some systems, critically ill patients rescue plan, Chinese characteristics of treatment and so on.

Our nurses are also very hard. Lu Wei, deputy director of the Nursing Department of Longhua Hospital, and Liu Qing, head nurse of the City Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, cooperate well and take responsibility seriously. Because there are not many staff members, once they put on protective clothing, they must not eat or drink for several hours, the toilet is to use adult diapers to solve, and its hardships can be imagined, hard and time it seems that we do not have these concepts.

As hard as it was for all of us, we were very motivated, and no one complained. We also had a temporary party branch meeting this evening, because we received more than 20 applications from the fire line to join the party. This also fully reflects a special period of medical staff a spiritual outlook and professional ethics.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: What are your thoughts on the application of traditional Chinese medicine in the treatment of new coronary pneumonia?

Fang Bangjiang: I'm from Hubei Province. After I got off the plane, I couldn't see the lively atmosphere before. There was no one in the street. People were forced to hide at home. Wuhan was like an empty city. My Heart ached very much.

After arriving in Wuhan, I especially hope to give full play to the advantages of the integration of Chinese and Western medicine, complementary advantages, as soon as possible to control the epidemic situation, reduce the incidence and mortality of critically ill patients.

Doctors are my profession, and I don't want to be a hero, but I do want to be like an angel, doing what I can to bring more patients back from the brink of death.
